<paragraph blockId="16.[168,776,1756,2016]" pageId="16" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1756,1780]" pageId="16" pageNumber="199">Identification.</emphasis>
Characterized by massive, scaly, erect stems, 2-pinnate leaves up to 
<quantity box="[500,562,1790,1814]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="199" unit="m" value="1.5">1.5 m</quantity>
long, subdimidiate pinnules that are sessile and obtuse, basal acroscopic pinnules overlapping the rachis, and minute spine-like projections on the upper surface of the junctures of the rachis, costae, and costules. Sori elongate, on both sides of the vein, indusia attached to vein along medial line. Not easily confused with any other fern from the area.
</paragraph>
